<task id="UDSS-016" project="UI Dialog Shell Standardization">
  <metadata>
    <title>Migrate DocumentUploadWizard from webpack to Vite</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <estimated-effort>5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>code-page, vite, migration, document-upload</tags>
    <dependencies>004</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Migrate the existing DocumentUploadWizard Code Page from webpack to Vite + vite-plugin-singlefile. This task is independent from the wizard extraction tasks (011a-015a) and can run alongside the P2-extract parallel group. The DocumentUploadWizard already exists as a Code Page — this is a build tool migration only, not a component extraction. Preserve all existing functionality while switching the build pipeline.</prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer with expertise in React 19, Fluent UI v9, and Dataverse Code Pages</role>
  <goal>DocumentUploadWizard builds successfully with Vite + vite-plugin-singlefile, producing identical single-HTML output, with webpack config removed</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-026">Vite + vite-plugin-singlefile for Code Pages — single HTML output, no webpack</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 tokens only, React 19, dark mode required</constraint>
    <constraint source="migration">Preserve all existing wizard functionality — this is a build tool swap, not a rewrite</constraint>
    <constraint source="file-ownership">File ownership: ONLY src/solutions/DocumentUploadWizard/ folder</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-026-full-page-custom-page-standard.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-v9-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/webresource/full-page-custom-page.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/EventsPage/</file>
      <file>src/solutions/DocumentUploadWizard/</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read the existing DocumentUploadWizard webpack configuration (webpack.config.js or similar) to understand current build setup, entry points, and plugins</step>
    <step id="2">Study the EventsPage Vite configuration as the canonical reference</step>
    <step id="3">Create vite.config.ts with vite-plugin-singlefile, matching entry point and output behavior</step>
    <step id="4">Update tsconfig.json if needed for Vite compatibility</step>
    <step id="5">Update package.json: replace webpack scripts with Vite build scripts, add vite and vite-plugin-singlefile dependencies, remove webpack dependencies</step>
    <step id="6">Remove webpack.config.js and any webpack-specific files (html-webpack-plugin templates, etc.)</step>
    <step id="7">Run npm install to resolve new dependency tree</step>
    <step id="8">Run npm run build — verify single HTML file output in dist/</step>
    <step id="9">Compare output size and structure with previous webpack build to ensure functional parity</step>
    <step id="10">Verify the output HTML file is self-contained (no external asset references)</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>webpack.config.js and all webpack dependencies removed</criterion>
    <criterion>vite.config.ts with vite-plugin-singlefile in place</criterion>
    <criterion>npm run build produces a single HTML file in dist/</criterion>
    <criterion>All existing wizard functionality preserved (no behavioral changes)</criterion>
    <criterion>Output HTML is self-contained — no external asset references</criterion>
    <criterion>No files outside src/solutions/DocumentUploadWizard/ were modified</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
